%N A397376 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (zeta(2) - H(2*k,2))*H(k)/(2*k+1), where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number, and H(k,2) = A007406(k)/A007407(k) is the k-th generalized harmonic number of order 2.
%H A397376 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.30, p. 431, eq. (4.121), section 5.30, p. 463, section 6.30, pp. 651-656.
